        "Abstract": "This paper introduces RuCoLA, a novel benchmark for linguistic acceptability classification in Russian, comprising 13.4k sentences labeled as acceptable or not. The dataset includes in-domain sentences from linguistic publications and out-of-domain sentences produced by generative models. We present a detailed analysis of acceptability classification experiments with various baseline approaches and release RuCoLA, the code, and a public leaderboard to assess the linguistic competence of language models for Russian."
